Kim Il Sung's Work Brought out in Venezuela 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung's famous work "For the Complete Victory of Socialism" was brought out in pamphlet by the Canta Clara Publishing House of Venezuela on August 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this work, published on December 30, Juche 75 (1986), the President clarified in detail main issues arising in achieving the complete victory of socialism and ways to do so.

Day of Korea's Liberation Observed in Russia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- A meeting of public figures of Russia was held in Moscow on August 9 to celebrate the 62nd anniversary of the liberation of Korea under the sponsorship of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venue of the meeting were photos showing immortal exploits of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos introducing Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were members of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union, figures of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK, the Institute of the Far East of the Russian Academy of Sciences and the Association of International Peace Fund and media persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK Vladimir Tolstikov in his speech at the meeting declared that the Russia-DPRK friendship forged in the struggle against the common enemy would last forever, recalling with pride that he took part in the operation for the liberation of Korea alongside units of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army commanded by the President 62 years ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 First Vice-Chairman of the above-said association Yuri Vanin noted that the sanguinary armed struggle led by the President against the Japanese imperialists made a decisive contribution to defeating  the formidable Japanese imperialists and winning victory in World War ï¿½U. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Director of the Institute of the Far East of the Russian Academy of Sciences Mikhail Tsitarenko said that the public circles of Russia are confident that the Korean people would continue winning victory after victory just as they defeated the U.S. and Japanese imperialists in the last century, adding that the Korean people are waging a resolute struggle to defend their system and achieve their goal under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Projected U.S. War Exercises Denounced in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) reportedly issued a statement on August 9 denouncing the projected reckless war exercises of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing the U.S. and south Korean bellicose forces of formally announcing their plan to stage large-scale "Ulji Focus Lens" joint military exercises in south Korea from August 20 to 31, the statement termed them dangerous moves for a war of aggression, pursuant to the U.S. strategy of preemptive strike to stifle the north by mobilizing all types of ultra modern war hardware. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These days the U.S. is going to stage the above-said war maneuvers in south Korea again despite the fact that points agreed upon at the six-party talks for the denuclearization and stability on the Korean Peninsula are being implemented, the statement noted, adding that this is a grave challenge to the peace-loving Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that the U.S. should roll back at once its scenario for a war against the north, though belatedly, if it truly wants the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula.

DPRK Women's Football Team Beats S. Korean Rival 3:1 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- The DPRK women's football team advanced to the quarter-finals after trouncing its Irish, Thai and German adversaries 3-0, 2-0 and 3-1 in the round robin series of the 24th World University Games now under way in Thailand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It trounced its south Korean rival 3-1 on August 13 to advance to the semi-finals.

Representatives of Foreign Missions Visit Area of Mt. Paektu 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Samjiyon, August 13 (KCNA) -- Foreign diplomatic envoys and representatives of international organizations in Pyongyang visited the area of Mt. Paektu from August 11 to 13 on the threshold of the 62nd anniversary of Korea's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the Samjiyon Grand Monument they placed a basket of flowers and bouquets before the statue of President Kim Il Sung and paid a tribute to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were briefed on the monument while making a round of the group sculptures depicting the boundless reverence of the anti-Japanese guerrillas and people for the President and their indomitable struggle and ardent patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They visited the secret camp of Mt. Paektu, the holy land of revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the old home of Kim Jong Il in the secret camp, while seeing the historic relics, they were briefed on the fact that Kim Jong Il grew while hearing the gun reports of the great anti-Japanese war as a lullaby. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors had a photograph taken before the old home. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Getting on the top of Mt. Paektu, the holy mountain of revolution, they were struck with wonders at the sight of the chain of peaks towering with grandeur surrounding the clean Lake Chon like a wall, the Paektu forests spreading far and wide and mountain ranges stretching endlessly.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also visited the Rimyongsu Revolutionary Site, the Monument to the Victory in the Battle in the Musan Area and the Paektu Hall and appreciated stage pieces performed by schoolchildren at the Samjiyon Schoolchildren's Palace.

Withdrawal of U.S. Forces from South Korea Demanded  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- Members of the student and civic and social organizations of south Korea reportedly held a "cultural festival on street" in Seoul on August 10 to demand the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution was read out after speeches at the above-said event held as part of the grand march for "beautiful Seoul without GIs." It said that people from various circles would scrap the unequal and shackling south Korea-U.S. "alliance" and make Seoul without GIs by all means. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the event the participants held a "ceremony of kicking off a grand cycle march" in front of the U.S. military base in Ryongsan before staging an anti-U.S. parade.

Candlelight Rally in S. Korea for Release of Civilians and Withdrawal of Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- A candlelight rally was reportedly held in Seoul on August 10 to demand the release of south Korean civilians under detention in Afghanistan and withdrawal of dispatched unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending there were members of political parties and civic and public organizations including the Democratic Labor Party and the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Speakers at the rally noted that the United States was these days taking counsel to launch a new, tougher military operation under the pretext of "rescuing" south Korean civilians abducted in Afghanistan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They denounced this as a despicable ruse to justify "the war on terrorism" in return for the death of the south Korean civilians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If any unhappy thing was caused among the civilians under detention by a rash new military operation, the U.S. would be held wholly responsible, they warned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers said that if the south Korean authorities truly wanted peace in this land, they should refuse the "war alliance" with the U.S. and withdraw the dispatched unit at once. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally the participants started a protest.

DPRK Children's Art Performances Acclaimed in China 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- The 6th East Asian Children's Art Festival was held in Shenyang, China from August 2 to 4 under the sponsorship of UNESCO. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival brought together children from the DPRK, China, Mongolia and other East Asian countries and regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean schoolchildren's performances that began with the chorus "Song of General Kim Jong Il" were highly acclaimed by the audiences during the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers put on the stage colorful numbers including song and dance "Pyongyang Is Best," dances "Dancing with Water Jar" and "Pleasant Holiday," kayagum solo "Ongheya" and triad dance "Fan Dance." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of the Educational Department of the Shenyang Municipal People's Government said that the child who presented "Dancing with Water Jar" showed high talent, indeed, noting that such talented child can be produced by the DPRK only where the children are regarded as the "kings" of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director-general of UNESCO said that the festival was initiated by the performance given by the DPRK children, requesting them to take part in the festival in the future, too as they won the admiration of the audiences with their superb artistry and talents and beautifully decorated each festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary-general of the UNESCO National Committee of Mongolia stressed that the performance given by the Pyongyang schoolchildren's art troupe deeply impressed the audiences with its strong national flavor and high artistic skill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A member of the children's art troupe of Macao, China said that all the numbers put on the stage by the Pyongyang schoolchildren's art troupe are pervaded with the patriotic spirit, adding that one can see such talented children and genuine arts only in the country where a good social system and policies are in force.

Mt. Paektu Lauded as Holy Mountain of Revolution by Foreign Delegates
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- Delegations and delegates of Juche idea study organizations in various countries when visiting the DPRK some time ago made a tour of Mt. Paektu and saw the old home of Kim Jong Il in the secret camp of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the holy land of revolution, the followers of the Juche idea expressed their excited feelings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chief of the Tynda City Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Russian Philosophy Association Gennadi Astakhov said the history of the anti-Japanese armed struggle commanded by President Kim Il Sung was vividly implanted in every range of Mt. Paektu and every turn of Amnok River. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He emphasized that the history of the original Songun policy pursued by Kim Jong Il traces its origin to Mt. Paektu and he was born as the great son of the guerrillas with the indomitable mettle of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chief of the Guinean Group for the Study of February 16 Art Riyad Chaloub noted that Mt. Paektu is the holy mountain of revolution shining with the history of legendary great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Mt. Paektu bears the marks of the glorious history of anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle led by the President and here is the old home where Kim Jong Il, great successor to the revolutionary cause of Juche, was born, the chief said here the Juche revolution found its origin and the bright future of the Korean revolution was firmly promised. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Teresa Otiniano, chairwoman of the Peruvian Association for the Study of Revolutionary Activities of Comrade Kim Jong Suk, said the chain of the peaks of Mt. Paektu soaring solemnly were symbolic of the indomitable spirit and matchless grit of the President and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We get strength and courage from the proud reality of the DPRK where the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered by the President in Mt. Paektu has been inherited and is being successfully carried to accomplishment by Kim Jong Il, the great brilliant commander of Songun, she said.

President Kim Il Sung's Victorious Leadership over Protracted Anti-Japanese War
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- Sixty-two years have passed since Korea was liberated from the rule of the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are retrospecting with deep emotion undying feats performed by President Kim Il Sung in the protracted hard-fought anti-Japanese war for national liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the 20-year-long anti-Japanese war, he had to overcome manifold difficulties and trials. He, together with 18 guerrillas, broke through the encirclement by the Japanese imperialist troops on a heights of Luozigou though tens of thousands-strong National Salvation Army ran away. He, with two companies of the guerrilla army, defended Xiaowangqing guerrilla zone from the offensive of 5,000-strong enemy forces which were backed with aircrafts and guns. He launched expedition to northern Manchuria two times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was when the President started on his way to East Manchuria from the first expedition to North Manchuria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stood sentry every night, gave to his men small amount of maize allotted to him and skipped over meals with snow and commanded the fierce battles with the enemy in a hot pursuit. He at last got a chill nearby Tianqiaoling. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One morning, he scarcely came to his senses and saw only 16 exhausted guerrillas remained around him. Then a thought flashed in upon him that if they sank to their knees there, the Korean people would become the lifelong slaves of the Japanese imperialists. He wrote the words of "Song of the Anti-Japanese War" and sang the song to inspire his comrades-in-arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Arduous March of the main force of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army from Nanpaizi, Mengjiang County, to Beidadingzi, Changbai County has been known as the rigorous period in the history of Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The guerrilla units had to fight battles over 20 times a day at maximum under the difficult condition in which the biting cold around 40 degrees C below zero coupled with starvation and contagious diseases. He commanded the Arduous March in the van for over 100 days, overcoming difficulties beyond human imagination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His sufferings were not limited only to physical ones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was bereaved of his beloved parents in an alien land, parted with younger brothers and lost his dear soldiers on the road of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He saved the revolution from crisis when the struggle against "Minsaengdan" swept over the land of East Manchuria, a great difficulty cropped up in the efforts for realizing the anti-Japanese united front with Chinese army and "Soviet enthusiasm," the "principle of one party for one country" and Expedition to Rehe were raised. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many years after, the President recollected with deep emotion that the responsibility for the revolution did not make him the vanquished and straggler of the revolution but victor, so as to keep him upholding the banner of anti-Japanese struggle.

Russian Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- Russian Ambassador e. p. to the DPRK Valery Sukhinin hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps Tuesday on the occasion of the 62nd anniversary of Korea's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kung Sok Ung and Chairman of the DPRK-Russia friendship parliamentary group Hong So Hon and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Staff members of the Russian embassy here were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

KCNA Terms Abe Political Greenhorn
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- Any rash act on the part of the chief executive of a country only brings shame to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Abe, now finding himself in a crisis due to his party's defeat in the recent House of Councilors election, is working hard to stay in power while trying to calm down the angry people with such rhetoric as "building a new state" and "re-starting from the very beginning." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
This rash deed can be done only by such political greenhorn as Abe lost to all sense of decency. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A man is bound to be ostracized by his people when he fools them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In a word, Abe suffered such miserable defeat as he followed hypocritical politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He mocked at his people and brought state affairs to failure, while imbuing his people with militarism and xenophobia under the pretext of "threat" from outside. The case of missing pension records and other scandals are an inevitable result of his misrule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Abe wishes to become a genuine statesman who thinks of building a new country, true to the will of his people, he should step down of his own accord, as strongly demanded by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, he is still clinging to a gimmick, far from drawing a lesson from the rebuff he met from his people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This proves that he is a wicked statesman blinded with the greed for power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a shame and a cause of social trouble for Japan to let such a petty guy insist on remaining in the prime minister's office, asserting "faith" and "will." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation has already turned unfavorable to him. No wonder, voices demanding his resignation are heard not only from Japan but from the United States, its senior ally. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not wise to insist only on his assertions, refusing to face up to the trend of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Abe would be well advised not to seek a lucky chance, keen on procrastination.

6th Video Meeting of Separated Families and Relatives Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- The 6th video meeting of separated families and relatives was held on Monday and Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in each meeting from the north and the south introduced their families and relatives to one another and showed their photos with kindred feelings, looking back on the course of life covered by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those from the north including Ri Ku Song residing in Rakrang District, Pyongyang and Ryu Si Nam residing in Unpha County, North Hwanghae Province talked to their kin from the south about their worthwhile life under the care of the DPRK. They added that not only they but also all their families are devoting themselves to the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation.

Floral Basket and Congratulatory Letter to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a floral basket and a congratulatory letter by the diplomatic corps here on the occasion of the 62nd anniversary of Korea's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floral basket and congratulatory letter were conveyed Tuesday to DPRK Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun by Egyptian Ambassador e. p. to the DPRK Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hatter who is doyen of the corps.

Losses Inflicted on National Economy by Torrential Rains Grow
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 14 (KCNA) -- The current torrential rains are causing an enormous damage to the various sectors of the national economy in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tens of pits of coal mines in Tokchon and Kaechon areas, South Phyongan Province were submerged and many facilities were destroyed as of August 13. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
More than 20 collieries were inundated completely. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over 60 pits were deluged and 400-odd facilities including winches and over 70 cutting faces were inundated in more than ten mines including Jungsan Mine of South Phyongan Province, Unpha Mine of North Hwanghae Province and Sudong Mine of South Hamgyong Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Owing to the rainstorms, more than 500 high voltage power towers collapsed, five electric power substations of large capacity were inundated and more than ten transformers and other facilities were severely hurt in North Hwanghae, South Phyongan and South Hamgyong provinces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Landslides of 14,000 cubic meters broke over 20 sections of railroads under the Hamhung Railway Bureau and nearly 100 sections under the Pyongyang and Kaechon railway bureaus, paralyzing transportation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Landslides and flood buried or washed away hundreds of thousands of cubic metres of timbers in forestry stations in Jagang and South Hamgyong provinces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Forest roads and railways were destroyed by landslides. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Heavy losses were reported from the building materials, land, city administration, fishery and other industries, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The damage is steadily growing.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona la Unidad No. 1286 del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 14 de agosto (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, inspecciono la Unidad No. 1286 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras enterarse del estado de cumplimiento del deber y de entrenamiento de la unidad, se mostro satisfecho de que todos los oficiales y soldados cumplen con responsabilidad su deber de combate con una elevada vigilancia y se prepararon al intensificar constantemente el ejercicio como combatientes capaces de pelear uno contra cien enemigos y dotados en alto grado de las tecnicas militares y capacidad combativa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al ver el frondoso bosque en torno a la unidad y el cuartel limpio y arreglado aun en la estacion de lluvias, valoro altamente el patriotismo de los uniformados de la unidad diciendo que ellos aprecian y cuidan como su vida cada arbol y cada planta de la patria y mantienen limpio el cuartel siguiendo el modo de vida de los guerrilleros antijaponeses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Alabo tambien el hecho de que la unidad ayuda con sinceridad los quehaceres de los pobladores de la zona, en que ella esta estacionada, incluyendo la administracion territorial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente dejo como recuerdo a los militares de la unidad binoculos, ametralladora y fusil automatico y se fotografio junto a estos.

Kim Jong Il dirige establecimientos industriales de Tanchon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 14 de agosto (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, dirigio en el terreno la Fabrica de Maquinas de Minas de Tanchon y la Fundicion de Metales No Ferrosos de Tanchon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En primer lugar, estuvo en la Fabrica de Maquinas de Minas de Tanchon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras escuchar los detalles de la trayectoria de ella en la sala de presentacion del historial, se cercioro del estado de equipos tecnicos y produccion recorriendo los procesos productivos como el taller de elaboracion de gran dimension. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante casi 60 anos, la clase obrera de esta planta suministro a tiempo los equipos y piezas de repuesto a las minas en la zona de Tanchon contribuyendo en gran medida al incremento de la produccion de minerales, valoro el Dirigente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Elogio tambien el hecho de que ella fabricara por cuenta propia muchas maquinas herramientas como el torno vertical de 10 metros. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A fin de proveer en lo suficiente de los equipos y accesorios conforme a la demanda de la realidad en que crece constantemente la produccion en las minas de la zona de Tanchon, hay que ejecutar con audacia y a modo de relampago la renovacion tecnologica de la fabrica, subrayo y enseno las tareas y remedios para este fin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A continuacion, el Dirigente se traslado a la Fundicion de Metales No Ferrosos de Tanchon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Despues de pasar por la sala de presentacion del historial, se dirigio a la cabina de control por computadora y otros procesos remodelados donde averiguo en detalles como marchan la reconstruccion y la produccion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se mostro muy complacido de que los trabajadores y los constructores de aqui edificaron magnificamente esta fundicion ultramoderna e impecable hasta en el remoto futuro y evaluo altamente sus esfuerzos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La orgullosa transformacion de esta planta, que registro un salto en su produccion mediante la renovacion tecnologica, comprobo el principio de la epoca de la industria de informatica de que la ciencia y la tecnica son precisamente la produccion o viceversa, destaco. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Continuo que cuando nuestras ciencias y tecnologias se combinen estrechamente con la produccion, podran servir de potente motor de la revolucion y la construccion y garantizar en lo cientifico-tecnico la construccion de una gran potencia prospera. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al ratificar que esta empresa ocupa un lugar importante en el desarrollo economico del pais, presento las tareas que incumben a ella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La tarea mas importante para la fundicion consiste en normalizar sostenidamente la produccion de alto nivel y recaudar todos los metales valiosos al introducir activamente las tecnologias de punta, asevero. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para poner en pleno funcionamiento a esta planta que incremento notablemente su capacidad de produccion a traves de la modernizacion y la cientifizacion, las minas de la zona de Tanchon como la de Komdok deben suministrarle en cantidad suficiente los minerales concentrados de buena calidad, encomendo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Entre los acompanantes del Dirigente figuraban Kim Ki Nam y Pak Nam Gi, secretario y jefe de departamento del CC del PTC, respectivamente.
